bxc4 19. Rxc4 Rxc4 20. Qxc4 Rc8 21. Qb4 Ba8 22. Rc1 Rb8 23. Qc4 h6 $11 {
Bogosavljevic,B (2541)-Perunovic,M (2580) Vrsac 2008 (1-0, 37)}) (17. Nd2 {
[%csl Rc1] Rahman,Z (2447)-Kunte,A (2568) Kolkata 2001 (½-½, 32) leaves the
c1-rook insufficiently well defended allowing} Bxd5 $5 18. cxd5 (18. exd5 Qa5
19. a3 bxc4 20. Nxc4 Qb5 $132) 18... Rxc1 19. Qxc1 Ng4 $132) 17... Rxc1 18.
Nxe7+ ({The knight was about to lose its stability in the centre:} 18. Qxc1
axb5 19. Qd2 (19. Qd1 {controls g4 but endangers the central pawn:} Nxd5 20.
exd5 Qa8 21. a3 Nf6 $17) 19... Bxd5 20. exd5 Ng4 $132) 18... Qxe7 19. Bxc1 axb5
20. Qd3 Rb8 21. Rd1 d5 (21... Nb6 $5 22. Qxd6 Qxd6 23. Rxd6 Nc4 24. Rd1 Bxe4
$132) 22. Qxb5 (22. exd5 e4 $44) 22... d4 23. Qe2 Qd6 24. g4 Ba6 $15 {[%csl
Ga2,Gb2,Ge4] with more than enough compensation for the pawn due to the weak
pawns on a2, b2, e4, Danielian, E (2415)-Marin,M (2530)/Moscow Aeroflot 2005 
(0-1, 40).} *

[Event "?"]
